he most popular personal name in England. A Parisian form of the name <i>Guillaume</i> was also sometimes used (see   Gillam  ), which in medieval Wales was adopted as <i>Gwilym</i> (see   Gwilliam  ).","Americanized form (translation into English) of French   Guillaume  ."]},{"name":"Wilcott","meanings":["English (Somerset and Gloucestershire): habitational name from Willicote in Clifford Chambers (Gloucestershire). The placename derives from Old English <i>wilig</i> ‘willow’ + <i>cot</i> ‘cottage, hut, shelter’. In some cases perhaps an altered form of   Wilcock  ."]},{"name":"Wilcox","meanings":["English (Yorkshire, Lancashire, and Flintshire): variant of   Wilcock  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. This form of the surname is based on the pronunciation."]}]},{"name":"Anthony","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual English form of the old Roman family name <i>Antonius</i>, which is of uncertain (probably Etruscan) origin. The spelling with <i>-th-</i> (not normally reflected in the pronunciation) represents a learned but erroneous attempt to associate it with Greek <i>anthos</i> ‘flower’. In the post-classical period it was a common name, borne by various early saints, most notably a 3rd-century Egyptian hermit monk, who is regarded as the founder of Christian monasticism."],"variants":[{"name":"Antony","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Anthony ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":69,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":78,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705206,"age":91,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705207,"age":105,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Anthony Wilcock was born in 1480, in Yorkshire, England. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Johan."},"et":{"1480–":"1480–Surnud","1481–Female":"1481–Surnud","1500–1563":"1500–1563","1500–Male":"1500–Surnud","1480–Male":"1480–Surnud","1558":"1558","1500":"1500","1585":"1585","1563":"1563","1571":"1571","1481":"1481","1480":"1480","1549":"1549","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Flockton, Kirklees, West Yorkshire, England":"Flockton, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1480–":"1480–Kuollut","1481–Female":"1481–Kuollut","1500–1563":"1500–1563","1500–Male":"1500–Kuollut","1480–Male":"1480–Kuollut","1558":"1558","1500":"1500","1585":"1585","1563":"1563","1571":"1571","1481":"1481","1480":"1480","1549":"1549","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Flockton, Kirklees, West Yorkshire, England":"Flockton, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningasku